‚úÖ Practical No. 2 ‚Äî To Study SQL DML Statements
üìå Objective

To study and execute SQL DML (Data Manipulation Language) commands.

üß† What is DML?

DML stands for Data Manipulation Language.
These commands are used to insert, update, delete, and retrieve data stored in tables.

‚úÖ DML Commands List
Command	Purpose
INSERT	Add data into table
UPDATE	Modify existing records
DELETE	Remove records
SELECT	Retrieve data from table
‚úÖ Example Table

Before performing DML operations, create a sample table:

CREATE TABLE students (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    course VARCHAR(30),
    marks INT
);

‚úÖ DML Commands with Examples
1Ô∏è‚É£ INSERT ‚Äî Add Records

Insert single row:

INSERT INTO students (id, name, course, marks)
VALUES (1, 'Ranjit', 'B.Tech', 85);


Insert multiple rows:

INSERT INTO students VALUES
(2, 'Nikita', 'BCA', 90),
(3, 'Amit', 'BBA', 75);

2Ô∏è‚É£ SELECT ‚Äî Retrieve Data

Select all records:

SELECT * FROM students;


Select specific columns:

SELECT name, marks FROM students;

3Ô∏è‚É£ UPDATE ‚Äî Modify Data
UPDATE students
SET marks = 95
WHERE id = 2;

4Ô∏è‚É£ DELETE ‚Äî Remove Records

Delete specific record:

DELETE FROM students
WHERE id = 3;


Delete all records (not table):

DELETE FROM students;
